# Memory Rules (Vibe-Coder v3.0)

## Before Starting ANY Task
```
mcp supermemory search "<task keywords>"
```
If prior work exists → build on it, don't redo.

## After Completing ANY Task
```
mcp supermemory add "<what was done and why>" tags:[<domain>]
```

## Obsidian Vault Auto-Save (⛔ MANDATORY after every non-trivial task)
```bash
bash obsidian-update.sh \
  --title "<task title>" \
  --content "<what was done, learned, decided>" \
  --tags "<domain>,<type>"
```
Creates `obsidian_vibe-coder/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM-<title>.md` and updates MOC.

## For Codebase Context
```
mcp openviking read
```
Load prior decisions and architecture context.

After making changes:
```
mcp openviking write "<what changed and why>"
```

## Memory Hierarchy
1. **Supermemory** — long-term, cross-session, #1 on benchmarks
2. **OpenViking** — codebase-specific context (ByteDance)
3. **Claude-Mem** — session memory (auto via hooks in Claude Code)

## When to Save
- Novel pattern discovered → save + create skill
- Architecture decision made → save with `tags:[architecture]`
- Bug fixed → save root cause with `tags:[debugging]`
- Performance optimization → save approach with `tags:[performance]`
